\begin_layout Itemize
##### We can solve a Poisson problem (via applying WLSQM to the heat equation)
 to obtain 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln\rho$
\end_inset

.
 Apply 
\begin_inset Formula $\nabla\cdot(\dots)$
\end_inset

 to both sides:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\nabla\cdot\nabla(\ln\rho)=\frac{1}{\alpha}\nabla\cdot\boldsymbol{g}=0\;,
\]

\end_inset

where the last equality follows because the gravitational field is uniform.
 As the boundary conditions, we can use
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\widehat{\boldsymbol{n}}\cdot\nabla(\ln\rho)=0\;,
\]

\end_inset

describing that far away from the obstacle, the flow returns to its free-stream
 state (no disturbances in 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln\rho$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

